node.text:
The video shows our entire process of the countertop we built for our client in Fernie! 
-
We used a 18’ slab of Canadian black walnut to achieve a continuous look all the way down the piece. The rocks were harvested directly from our clients property on the Elk river. 
- 
We also installed an internal LED strip that is integrated to the smart lighting system in the home. 
-
Wood: Canadian Black Walnut
Resin: Black Forest Deep Resin
Finish: Black Forest Oil
Top Coat: Black Forest Ceramics
-

node.text:
This table was a custom commission for our clients new home addition in North Carolina!
They needed a dining table that could comfortably seat 20 people and wanted it in a single piece. We used one of our 22’ bastogne walnut slabs and the final size measured in at 20’x5’. 
-
We were able to pour the 260L of resin required for this piece in a single shot by using our Black Forest Deep Resin.

This piece was a custom commission for @gpstephan. He will be using it as a desk for his podcast, The Iced Coffee Hour!
-
The top is created with California Pecan wood, Black Forest Deep Resin, and of course, coffee beans. 
We finished this piece using our new Black Forest Furniture Oil. Over the years of creating custom tables, we have tried just about every finish on the market. 
We have never found something we were 100% happy with, this led to the creation of our Black Forest Furniture Oil. 
It is a plant based product that dries much harder and protects against moisture better than many of the products we have tried. 
It is a monocoat system, however we recommend two coats of a higher sheen is desired!
-
We are in the final stages of packaging design and hope to have this available within a month!
Leave your questions below 👇 
-

This cabinet was commissioned as a part of the largest furniture package order we have ever received!
The Package includes a dining table, 14 chairs, a large cabinet to display fossils, two credenzas, custom walmart, a desk, and a coffee table!
-
Nearly the entire package will be constructed from our premium buckeye burl and paired with transparent turquoise resin. 
-
We competed this pour using our Black Forest Deep Resin. It has a very low viscosity with a slow cure, making it perfect for large pours where zero bubbles are desired. 
Although buckeye is porous and prone to bubbles, our Black Forest Deep Resin allows for a crystal clear pour without the need to seal edges. 
-

-
We currently have much more claro walnut burl available for a piece like this!

node.text:
We were commissioned by our client in Nebraska to complete a large furniture package for their new rental property. 
The property is located in @dismalriver and will be available for rentals! 
We also completed the majority of the furniture in this home (photos coming soon). 
-
The entire door unit is constructed from solid Canadian maple, no plywood or veneer was used anywhere in the door. 
We exclusively use solid wood for all of our doors, while there may be cheaper alternatives, we believe in building pieces made to last. 
We finish our doors using oil based products to allow for easy maintenance as the piece ages. 
In the past, we have tried sprayed urethanes and have found that after 5-10 years the finish can begin to flake. This makes for a costly repair. 
With oil based finish, the finish may dull over time but is easily restored with a fresh coat. 
-

We are doing something we have never done before with this podcast desk for @gpstephan. 
The top is created from California Pecan wood, 60L of our Black Forest Deep Resin, and of course coffee beans. 
-
In order to do this successfully, we first poured a base layer and let it tack up. We then added the coffee beans and poured another thin layer to seal them and fix them in place during the pour. 
After the seal coat on the beans was tacky we then added the final 45L of resin. 
-

node.text:
We were commissioned to build the largest resin cast table we have ever made! It will be used as a dining room table in our clients home. 
The piece measures in at 20’Lx5’W. 
-
We ended up using 260L of our Black Forest Deep Resin to cast the slab. 
Since our resin does not produce much heat during the cure, we are able to pour a piece like this at nearly 3” thick in a single shot! 
-
Next, we will be getting this piece onto our @avidcnc for flattening. 
-

This piece is a custom commission for our clients new home in Fernie! 
We are also building them a dining table, desk, shelves, and a bench. 
Our team will be personally delivering these pieces in about 2 weeks!
-
You will notice on this piece that numerous rocks actually stick through the edge of the piece. In order to achieve this, we had to cut the top with a diamond blade. This method is much more challenging but looks great when finished!
-
Wood: Canadian Black Walnut
Resin: Black Forest Deep
Finish: Osmo Extra Thin
Buffer: Mirka DEROS
Applicator: White Scotchbrite Pad 
-

We wanted to experiment with our resin and see if we could successfully cast a perishable item. Obviously, we chose a slice of Black Forest cake. 
- 
We sealed the cake with our Coat Resin before casting it with our Deep Resin. 
After the piece was cured we sanded to 4000 grit, polished with automotive compounds, and then applied our Black Forest Ceramics. 
-
Leave your guesses below as to what you think will happen to the cake over time!

node.text:
This is the largest maple burl log we have ever seen 😱
We recently purchased this once in a lifetime maple burl log from an arborist in Oregon. 
We had the log sent down to our friends @gl_veneer who will be doing the milling for us!
These slabs measure in at over 12’ long and 9’ wide at the widest points! 
-
The tree unfortunately had to come down due to the large rotten section in the center of the log, making less stable and unsafe. 
We are very fortunate to have to opportunity to salvage pieces like this and turn them into generational furniture. 
-
These slabs will require multiple years of drying and will not be workable until sometime after 2023. It’s a long term investment for us that is sure to pay off. 
-

Console Table with Canadian Walnut and Midnight Blue Resin 
This piece was a custom commission for our client in British Colombia! 
They selected a slab of Canadian Black Walnut and paired it with midnight blue resin and solid steel legs. 
As this slab was cut near the outside of the tree, it features a lot of live edge character that can be seen beneath the resin.

We are currently taking commission for orders completing in mid fall! You can find out furniture quote form on our website!

node.text:
Coffee Bean Desk for @gpstephan ☕️ 
We were commissioned to create a custom podcast desk that will be used for Graham’s podcast, The Iced Coffee Hour. 
-
The top is created from California Pecan wood, coffee beans, and our Black Forest Deep Resin. 
To create this effect, we first poured a base layer and allowed it to partially cure. We then placed the beans in and poured a thin layer over them to seal them and secure them in place. 
Once the seal coat had cured we poured our final layer to completely submerge everything!
-
Wood: Pecan
Resin: Black Forest Deep Resin
Finish: Black Forest Furniture Oil (coming soon)
Top Coat: Black Forest Ceramics 
-

node.text:
$40,000 Bastogne Walnut Dining Table 😱
Measuring in at 20’x5’, this is the largest resin and wood dining table that we have ever created!
-
We were commissioned to create this piece as a custom dining table for our clients new addition on their home in North Carolina. 
Our client also opted to keep this slab in a single piece as opposed to splitting it in two for easier shipping and transport. 
The table weighs nearly 2000lbs all together and will require a team of 10 people to safely lift it into the home. 
-
Wood: Bastogne Walnut from @gl_veneer 
Resin: Black Forest Deep 
Finish: Black Forest Furniture Oil (coming soon)
Top Coat: Black Forest Ceramics
Legs: Solid Steel Frames from @forge_53 
-

5’ Round Sycamore Burl Dining Table 
This piece was a custom commission for our client in London, UK. 
They selected a premium piece of California sycamore burl and paired it with very dark midnight blue resin and a solid ash Trapezoid base with a Shou-Sugi-Ban finish. 
-
We poured this piece using our Black Forest Deep Resin, finished it with our Black Forest Furniture Oil, and topped it off with our Black Forest Ceramics. 
-
We are currently taking orders for custom commissions finishing in early fall, you can send us a message or fill out the quote form on our website in the “Table Gallery”. 
-

node.text:
Decayed Claro Walnut Desk 🤤
We were commissioned by our client in Edmonton to create a custom desk for his new home office. 
He selected a decayed slab of claro walnut and paired with tinted Black Forest Deep Resin. 
The legs are solid steel with a black lacquer finish. 
-
Here is the review our client gave us after the delivery:
“Finally made the decision to pull the trigger on a custom desk for my office.  My only previous exposure  to Black Forest up until that point was watching their product line through social media.

I reached out, got a response immediately and the entire process, from selecting the specific piece of wood, through design, and to delivery was 100% top end.

My desk arrived and was set up last week and it’s more beautiful and timeless than I ever even imagined.

Amazing company, amazing quality and craftsmanship.

I’d give 6 stars if I could.” 
-
Resin: Black Forest Deep Resin 
Wood: Claro Walnut 
Pigment: ColorFX Black Dye 
Legs: Solid Steel
Finish: Black Forest Furniture Oil
Top Coat: Black Forest Ceramics
-
#furniture #homeoffice #woodworking #liveedge #epoxy #desksetup
